<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 9.81 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday lost 9.81 points to
3,080.91 as against last Friday's close of 3,090.72.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost 2.73 points to 1,369.49 from the
previous close of 1,372.22.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted marginally up at
317.49 and 124.31 compared with the previous close of 317.37 and
124.24 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities declined in lackluster trading at the BSE market
Monday due to lack of speculative support and mild profit-taking
at higher levels.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the long pending decision on buy-back of shares
had resulted in poor trading activity at all the bourses in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
