<HEADLINE> Florence Griffith Joyner Dies of Seizure at 39 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Florence Griffith
Joyner, the world records holder of women's 100 and 200 meters
races, has died at the age of 39 due to a seizure.
</P>
<P>
USA Track and Field spokesman Pete Cava confirmed the death
of the American sprint star who won set her two world records and
won three gold medals at the 1988 Seoul Olympics, in the 100m,
200m and 4x100m relay.
</P>
<P>
Griffith Joyner, known for her self-designed fancy running
uniforms and long fingernails, also won a 1984 Olympic silver
medal in the heptathlon and 1992 bronze medal in the long jump.
</P>
</TEXT>
