<HEADLINE> U.S. Embassy Bombing Suspects Brought to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Two suspects alleged
to have got involved in the August 7 bombing at the United States
embassy in Tanzania were arraigned on a charge of murder Monday
before the Kisutu Resident's Magistrate Court in Dar es Salaam.
</P>
<P>
They are Mustafa Mahmoud Said Ahmed and Rashid Saleh Hemed,
but their nationalities were not disclosed. They have been
charged with murdering 11 people.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, media reports said that one of the suspects is a
Tanzanian citizen from Zanzibar while the other is a foreigner.
</P>
<P>
Reading the charge sheet, Assistant Commissioner of Police
Leonard Mashaka alleged in the court that the suspects committed
the offence on August 7 at US embassy premises in the Kinodoni
district of the capital city.
</P>
<P>
The blast, caused by a bomb planted under a water tanker, also
injured more than 70 people.
</P>
<P>
Principal Resident Magistrate Amin Manento asked the suspects
not to enter any plea because the case will be tried by the High
Court.
</P>
<P>
The case was adjourned to October 5, when it will come up for
another mention as the police are still investigating the case.
The suspects were remanded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
