<HEADLINE> 1 in 3 Greek Companies in Tourist Areas Evades Taxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- One out of three companies in
Greece's tourist areas was tax evader, according to a report
released by the country's Finance Ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
In August, Greece's Financial Crimes Squad conducted a total of
10,737 inspections in 8,953 companies, and they found 3,760 cases
of tax evasion.
</P>
<P>
Evasion in large enterprises was 58.4 percent, followed by the
self-employed such as doctors and lawyers at 56.3 percent, hotels
at 47.16 percent, tourism enterprises at 45.5 percent, places of
entertainment at 35.23 percent and fuel companies at 33.3 percent,
the report said. 
</P>
