<HEADLINE> Sampras, Rafter Withdraw Grand Slam Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MUNICH, September 22 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
and U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter have both withdrew from
next week's lucrative Grand Slam Cup, organizers said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Also quitting from the 6.7 million U.S. dollar event, which
brings together the best performers from the year's four grand
slams, will be French Open champion Carlos Moya of Spain, the
world number five.
</P>
<P>
The best ranked player in the men's draw will be world number
three Marcelo Rios of Chile. Five of the world's top 10 players
will be in Munich, among them number eight Andre Agassi who had a
dismal grand slam season but was given a wild card.
</P>
<P>
For the first time women's events will be held in the Grand
Slam Cup where world number one Martina Hingis and American
Lindsay Davenport, who beat the 17-year-old Swiss in the U.S.
Open final, are the favorites.
</P>
<P>
The tournament starts next Tuesday. 
