<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 14.34 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday gained 14.34 points to
3,095.25 as against Monday's close of 3,080.91.
</P>
<P>
The national index also rose by 4.40 points to 1,373.89 from
the previous close of 1,369.49.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar were quoted up at 318.26 and 124.65
from the previous close of 317.49 and 124.31 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Selected pivotals managed to stage a comeback after a mild
setback during mid-session on the BSE market Tuesday due to
shortcovering at lower levels coupled with scattered purchases by
foreign and domestic funds.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the weak trends in the global markets had lowered
the inflow of funds from foreign investors. 
