<HEADLINE> Senior Official Praises Photo Exhibits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Senior Chinese Party official
Ding Guan'gen today praised the ongoing exhibition of photos
showing Chinese civilians and soldiers battling heavy summer
flooding.
</P>
<P>
"The show displays the great flood control spirit, as well as
patriotism, collectivism, socialism and revolutionary heroism,"
said Ding. He also noted exhibits provide a highly effective tool
for educating the general public.
</P>
<P>
Ding, a member of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee Political Bureau and head of the Publicity Department
under the CPC Central Committee, made the remarks while visiting
the exhibition which began on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The media played an important role in this year's flood relief
effort, said Ding.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition features 300 photos shot by Chinese
journalists. Hundreds of reporters were dispatched to flooded
areas along the Yangtze and Nenjiang rivers.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is sponsored by the nation's leading media
organizations, including Xinhua News Agency and People's
Daily. 
