<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Manufactures Dongfeng 4D Locomotives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China has produced 300 disel
Dongfeng 4D locomotives which will power Chinese trains at much
faster speeds beginning on October 1, 1998,
</P>
<P>
China recently announced plans to raise the speed of trains
beginning next month. Dongfeng locomotives, which have passed all
operational tests, will pull 19 rail cars at an average speed of
125 km per hour and maximum speed of 135 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The Dongfeng series was developed in 1996 and entered
production at the Dalian Rolling Stock Plant in 1997. The Dalian
plant currently holds a 60 percent share of the domestic
locomotive market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
