<HEADLINE> Norwood Stops Japanese Challenger Matsumoto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Freddy
Norwood left his title vacant after beating Japanese challenger
Koji Matsumoto in the 10th round of a scheduled 12-round World
Boxing Association (WBA) featherweight bout here Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The over-weighted Norwood failed to clear the limit of 57.1
kilograms for the featherweight category in the weigh-in and lost
his crown in Monday. He was 800 grams over the limit.
</P>
<P>
Referee Stanley Christodolou of South Africa stopped the fight
25 seconds into the 10th round as Norwood hammered the helpless
Japanese with a barrage of blows.
</P>
<P>
If Matsumoto, 28, had won, he could have become the new
champion.
</P>
<P>
It was Norwood's 32nd victory, including 20 knockouts, against
one draw.
</P>
<P>
Matsumoto has a record of 26 victories, including 15 knockouts
and six defeats and one draw. 
</P>
