<HEADLINE> Law Makers Lectured on People's Congress System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, China's highest legislative body, held
its third law lecture today.
</P>
<P>
Chairman Li Peng presided over the session which focused on the
characteristics and history of the nation's system of people's
congresses.
</P>
<P>
Li urged participants to enhance their understanding of the
importance of the legislative system in China, and stressed that
the people's congress system is the organizational form of the
people's dictatorship and the nation's principal political system.
</P>
<P>
The powers of state belong to the people who practice their
right to rule through the national and local people's congresses,
said Li, adding that the right is the historic result of
the long struggle carried out under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Liu Zheng, a member of the NPC Law Committee, presented
the lecture and stressed that upholding and improving the people's
congress system represents the principal way to develop socialist
democracy. He noted related efforts will be great importance for
ensuring continued economic development, and social progress and
stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
