and Trade Fair, which opened today in east China's Shandong
Province, has attracted over 800 foreign business people from 30
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Jinan has proposed 50 cooperative projects involving
infrastructure construction, enterprise upgrading, agriculture and
high technology.
</P>
<P>
The city encourages its enterprises to invest abroad and has
recruited foreign businessmen to join in the establishment of
joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Jinan has accelerated its pace of opening in recent years and
introduced foreign funds of over 359 million US dollars between
January and August this year, up 10.9 percent on the same period
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
