Monday night, Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi again
criticized the nuclear tests by India and Pakistan. "India and
Pakistan conducted a series of nuclear tests in May to our deepest
regrets posing formidable challenges to the nuclear
non-proliferation regime," he said. 
