<HEADLINE> Air Macao to Run Regular Chartered Flight to Ningbo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao announced in a press
release Tuesday that it will inaugurate a regular twice-a-week
chartered flight service between Macao and eastern Chinese port
city of Ningbo on October 6 using Airbus 321 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Flight NX9118 will leave Macao every Tuesday and Saturday at
12:35 and arrive at Ningbo at 14:45. The return flight of NX9117
will depart Ningbo the same day at 15:45 and arrive at Macao at
18:05.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo is the air company's ninth destination in China's
mainland after Beijing, Shanghai, Xiamen, Wuhan, Fuzhou, Nanjing,
Chongqing and Zhengzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
