<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Loess Plateau Project (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhang Qiuming, deputy director of the Shanxi Provincial Finance
Bureau, says that by the end of June the project had covered more
than 60,000 ha., or 63 percent of the planned area, with terraced
land, sediment control dams, and land-stabilizing trees, shrubs,
orchards and pasture.
</P>
<P>
He says that Shanxi had used more than 345 million yuan
including 215 million yuan in World Bank loans and that the
project has added 1.1 mu of terraced land for each person in the
project area, and 0.4 mu of orchards and 1 mu of forest.
</P>
<P>
Soil erosion in project areas has been brought under control,
with agricultural production conditions improved and grain yields
increasing sharply.
</P>
<P>
In the project area, the sediment flow into the Yellow River is
expected to be cut by more than five million tons annually.
</P>
<P>
Juergen Voegele, the World Bank official in charge of the
project, said that the project is successful, its quality is
excellent, and he is satisfied with the work of local officials
and is pleased to see that this has happened so fast. Nobody
thought a few years ago that the success would be so visible and
so fast, he says.
</P>
<P>
Because of the success of the first phase, the World Bank and
Shanxi provincial government will assess the second phase. The
total watershed rehabilitation area covered by the two projects
will account for more than 11 percent of the province's total soil
erosion, he says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
