<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sees Rapid Economic Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China has experienced a rapid
economic growth over the past 20 years, according to an official
release from the State Statistics Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
China is now seventh in the world in terms of economic
strength, according to the release, which added that the gross
domestic product has reached 7.47 trillion yuan, with an annual
growth rate of 9.8 percent for the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1997 China's agricultural output
reached 2.47 trillion yuan, nearly four times that of 1978's
figure, while that of industry reaching 11.2 trillion yuan, 14
times greater than the 1978 figure.
</P>
<P>
In the 1981-1997 period, investments in fixed assets totalled
14 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the investment structure was improved with
the construction of a group of key infrastructural projects such
as the Qinshan Nuclear Power Station and the Beijing-Kowloon
railway.
</P>
<P>
Along with economic development, a "buyer's market" is taking
shape in China, said the release, noting that in 1997 retail sales
in the country reached 2.,72 trillion yuan, some 20 times that of
1978.
</P>
<P>
China now has trade relations with more than 200 countries and
regions, and has used 348.3 billion U.S. dollars of foreign funds
in the past 20 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
