<HEADLINE> China Goes All Out to Ensure Safety of Nuke Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China has effectively
guaranteed the safety of nuclear power plants as the country's
nuclear industry is moving into a hective year.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official in charge of nuclear industry,
China is busy carrying out its nuclear power projects this
year. However, first of all, China has ensured the safe and stable
operation of the Qinshan and Daya Bay nuclear power plants.
</P>
<P>
He said that the country has continued to undertake a number of
nuclear construction projects this year, namely, Qinshan 2,
Qinshan 3, Ling'ao and Lianyungang nuclear power projects.
</P>
<P>
The official has urged all nuclear departments to have a
greater sense of responsibility, improve management systems, and
enhance the safety of nuclear materials and nuclear facilities.
</P>
<P>
He said the relevant parties have set up a joint meeting system
and a regular coordination meeting system to exclusively research
the construction of nuclear power projects, and solve problems
jointly and quickly.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the country's two functioning
nuclear power plants, Qinshan and Daya Bay, have maintained stable
and safe operation. And both of the plants have been refueled and
overhauled for a second time. So far, the two plants have
generated nearly 15 billion kilowatt hours of electricity.
</P>
<P>
Surveys have found that the amount of waste discharged by
Qinshan and Daya Bay nuclear power plants meet government-set
standards and have passed
safety checks conducted by the International Atomic Energy Agency.
</P>
<P>
They posed no harm to the surrounding environment and have
helped to build a good image for China's nuclear power industry,
he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
