<HEADLINE> 87 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 87 kilograms of
hashish has been seized in an operation against drug trafficking
in southeastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a statement issued Tuesday by Turkish police
as saying that police teams had confiscated the hashish in bags in
their operation in the city of Malatya. However, it did not
disclose when the drugs were caught.
</P>
<P>
Nine Turks were detained in connection with the drugs, said
the agency.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Turkish police have seized 10.5
kilograms of hashish and arrested two suspected drug traffickers
in Bolu, about 200 kilometers west of Ankara, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs to Europe from the border
areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police seized
4.4 tonnes of heroin, which accounted for 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
