<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Meets With Romanian Senate Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), in a meeting today with the Chairman of
Romania's Senate Petre Roman, emphasized co-operation between the
CPPCC and the Romanian Senate.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two organizations are an important
component of overall bilateral ties and are sound, Li said. He
said he also hopes that both sides will increase contacts and
contribute more to the friendship between the two countries that
can be traced back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
He praised the frequent high-level exchanges, the increasing
cooperation in various fields, and Romania's support for China on
many important issues, especially its "one China" stand. China
hopes that Romania will overcome the temporary difficulties it has
encountered and achieve its development goal of creating a better
future.
</P>
<P>
Romania is well aware of the significance of developing
friendly cooperation with China, Roman said, and he hopes to
expand bilateral cooperation in political, economic, diplomatic,
and cultural areas.
</P>
<P>
Roman also praised China's achievements since it initiated
reforms and opening up, and said that although Romania differs
from China in its national conditions, it can still learn a lot
from China.
</P>
<P>
Roman is in China as Li's guest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
