<HEADLINE> Baggio Avoids Head-on Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer star Roberto
Baggio narrowly avoided a head-on collision with a truck but was
unscathed in the accident on Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Baggio's Mercedes was crossing the small town of Semiana when
the oncoming truck wandered into his lane, forcing the Inter
Milan ace to try and swerve out of the way.
</P>
<P>
He avoided a head-on collision, but the left side of his
Mercedes was still hit by the truck, causing minor damage. Baggio
and two other occupants were unhurt, while police charged the
Polish lorry driver with a driving offense. 
</P>
