<HEADLINE> French Ambassador Comments On Jospin's Upcoming China Visit (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- France's Ambassador to China
Pierre Morel told Xinhua today that Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin's' visit to China will bring French-Chinese relations to a
new stage in all areas.
</P>
<P>
Jospin is expected to visit China September 24-26 at the
invitation of Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Morel said that the joint communique issued by the Chinese and
French governments in 1994 solved a number of difficulties in
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
When President Jacques Chirac visited China in May 1997 and
signed a joint declaration on a comprehensive Sino-French
partnership for the 21st century with Jiang Zemin, the title
itself spoke of its contents.
</P>
<P>
France's dialogues with China are quite positive on
constructing a truly multipolarized world together, he says, and
there are daily exchanges in different levels. Jospin's upcoming
visit and Premier Zhu Rongji's visit to France last April reflect
the sound relations between France and China, he said, including
reinforced economic and trade ties, unprecedentedly rich cultural
exchanges, and frequent, and frequent effective political
dialogues.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Ambassador on Jospin's Upcoming China Visit (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Morel said that Jospin's visit will be one of a series of
visits to China this autumn by European leaders, and he will
discuss China's attitude about a single European currency, which
is expected to be launched January 1, 1999, and China's relations
with Europe.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said he believes that exchanges between Europe
and China will continue to grow and that Europe is an economic
giant and a center of technical innovation. Europe is ready to
serve the development of a more harmonious world, and no doubt,
China can get a lot of experience from Europe, and find many
opportunities for cooperation there, he said.
</P>
<P>
Morel assumed his position in November 1996. He said, the
French and Chinese people have known each other a long time and
cherish a special feeling for each other. It is exciting for him
to devote his efforts to the formation of a long-term bilateral
partnership that is really effective, he concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
