<HEADLINE> International Conference On Office Automation In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- An international conference
on office automation via television will open October 22 in
Beijing, Guangzhou, and the U.S.'s Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be sponsored jointly by the National
Information Center, the State Economic and Trade Commission, the
U.S.'s VTEL, and 30 Chinese government information centers.
</P>
<P>
A 500-sq.m. exhibition with 50 stands of new office automation
technology and products will be held in Beijing's Hall of Science
and Technology during the conference..
</P>
<P>
Wu Kezhong, an advisor to the State Council General Office's
Office Automation Agency, calls it a grand gathering for the 21th
century and says he hopes that it will play an active role in
improving the country's office automation.
</P>
<P>
It will also help speed up the development of China's
information sector and the national economy, he says.
</P>
<P>
The Organizing Committee of the conference has received nearly
100 papers on efficiency through office automation for China's
institutional restructuring, flood information system, electronic
business, and information-based economy.
</P>
<P>
Participants in Beijing, Guangzhou and Silicon Valley will be
able to share opinions simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
A dozen Chinese and foreign companies, including VTEL, Sybase
(China), the U.S.'s Bay, and China's Software and Founder have
expressed a desire to display their products at the exhibition,
according to the Organizing Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
