<HEADLINE> China Sees Rapid Economic Development Over Past 20 Years (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China has registered rapid
economic growth over the past 20 years, according to an official
release from the State Statistics Bureau today.
</P>
<P>
China is now listed No. 7 in terms of economic strength in the
world, said the release, adding that the gross domestic product
reached 7,477.2 billion yuan, registering an annual growth rate of
9.8 percent for the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1997, China's agriculture output reached
2,470.9 billion yuan, 3.4 times that of 1978's figure, while that
of industries reaching 11.2 trillion yuan, 14 times that of
1978's figure.
</P>
<P>
In the 1981-1997 period, the investment in fixed assets
totalled 14 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the investment structure was improved with a batch
of key infrastructural projects being constructed during
the period, such as the Qinshan Nuclear Power Station and the
Beijing-Kowloon railway.
</P>
<P>
With this economic development, a "buyer's market" is taking
shape in China, said the release, noting that in 1997, the retail
sales of consumer goods in the country reached 2,729.9 billion
yuan-worth, more than 20 times those in 1978.
</P>
<P>
China is now opening still wider to the outside world, as it
has set up trade relations with more than 200 countries and
regions, and has used 348.3 billion U.S. dollars of foreign funds
in the past 20 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0145 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sees Rapid Economic Development Over Past 20 Years (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1997, China's foreign trade volume was 325.1 billion
U.S. dollars, increasing from 20.6 billion U.S. dollars in 1978.
</P>
<P>
The living standards of the Chinese people are improving as
their incomes rise, said the release.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the per capita disposable income for urban residents
in the country reached 5,160 yuan, registering an annual growth
rate of 6.2 percent for the past 20 years, while the per capita
net income for people in rural areas came to 2,090 yuan, growing
8.1 percent each year.
</P>
<P>
China has also made great achievements in other fields, such as
medical care and social security systems, the release noted.
</P>
<P>
It also mentioned China's achievements in reforms of economic
structure, saying a socialist market economy system has taken
shape.
</P>
<P>
The release pinpointed favorable factors for the country's
economic development, noting the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China held last year has set a clear guide for
the economic development.
</P>
<P>
The economic growth in the past 20 years has also laid a strong
foundation for further development, said the release.
</P>
<P>
It admitted that China's economy is also faced with some
unfavorable factors, such as imbalance of regional economic
development, poor operation of some firms and weak infrastructure
basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
