<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed higher Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index ended 7.13
points higher at 385.45, the all-share Emas Index gained 1.77
points to 102.03, the Industrial Index rose 11.39 points to 760.46
and the Second Board Index gained 1.06 points to 94.53.
</P>
<P>
Gainers beat losers by 445 to 106 while 121 counters were
unchanged, 246 counters untraded and 38 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was lower at 115.901 million shares worth
159.562 million ringgit (41.99 million U.S. dollars) from 175.829
million shares worth 230.214 million ringgit (60.582 million U.S.
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover eased to 111.416 million shares worth
152.720 million ringgit (40.189 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 169.176 million shares valued at 220.733 million ringgit
(58.087 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board volume dropped to 4.485 million shares valued
at 6.842 million ringgit (1.8 million U.S. dollars) from 6.653
million shares worth 9.480 million ringgit (2.494 million U.S.
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
Off market turnover increased to 5.535 million shares valued at
7.870 million ringgit (2.07 million U.S. dollars) from 1.123
million shares valued at 2.500 million ringgit (0.657 million U.S.
dollars) Monday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.758
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products 8.157
million shares, construction 16.261 million shares,
trading/services 29.079 million shares, infrastructure 901,000
shares, finance 15.960 million shares, hotels 270,000 shares,
properties 20.775 million shares, plantation 2.202 million shares,
mining 458,800 shares, trusts 173,000 shares, closed/fund 24,000
shares and loans 12.397 million shares. 
