<HEADLINE> New Customs Building to Be Constructed in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a new customs
building will begin next week on a patch of reclaimed land between
the Macao peninsula and Macao's Taipa Island, the Macao Daily News
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Costing 98 million patacas (about 12.25 million U.S. dollars),
the building will be situated on the Macao side of the "Lotus
Flower Bridge" project which will connect the Taipa Island with
Zhuhai City's Hengqin Island. Construction of the bridge started
on June 29 this year.
</P>
<P>
Other facilities include a tax-free store, a mail center, two
marine police posts and two overpasses for pedestrians.
</P>
<P>
The customs building is expected to be completed by August next
year.
</P>
<P>
The 1.3-kilometer "Lotus Flower Bridge" will open a second
crossing apart from the current border gate to China's inland
areas when it opens to traffic before Macao's handover in
December, 1999. 
</P>
