<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices went up on the
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) gained 13.73 points to end at 896 .32 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 143.99 million units worth 167.99
million Singapore dollars (about 96.98 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outnumbered losers by 165 to 50 with 205 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
SingTel was the most active stock of the day as it had a
turnover of 18.53 million stocks. It was followed by Kay Hian that
had 7.81 million units done. ERL w01 was next with 7.62 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA F led the market's increase in the day as it gained 45
cents to close at 8.55 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 went up 40
cents to finish at 16.60 Singapore dollars. SIA edged up 35 cents
to end at 5.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downward slope, SPH led the market's descent of the day
as it lost 30 cents to close at 13.20 Singapore dollars. OUE slid
by 14 cents to finish at 2.00 Singapore dollars. PenTex SC shed
off eight cents to end at 0.55 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said share prices moved up amid expectations of a cut
in employers' contributions to the Central Provident Fund.
</P>
<P>
They believed such a cut would lower business costs and
companies with a big number of employees would definitely benefit
in terms of labor cost savings.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also attributed today's rise to gains of regional
markets which were buoyed up.
</P>
<P>
They also noted that traders were picking up values after the
market's recent hit brought prices to bargain levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
