<HEADLINE> Community Doctors Make Life Better In Northern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese port city of Tianjin
has 1,232 community doctors, forming a community medical care
network that provides residents with disease prevention, health
care, recuperation, psychological and health education services.
</P>
<P>
One resident, Su Henian, and his wife used to go hospital for
blood pressure problems, but now whenever they have problems, they
just dial a phone number, and a doctor comes over.
</P>
<P>
The doctor who saves the old couple from having to deal with
traffic problems has been doing this for 5 years.
</P>
<P>
The diseases the city residents suffer from have changed from
contagious disease to chronic disease and problems of old age,
says Huang Jinhu, director of the municipal health bureau's
community service department.
</P>
<P>
"These patients don't need to be hospitalized, and the best way
is to arrange home-based medical care for them," he says. More
than 36,000 patients receive treatment at home.
</P>
<P>
Health awareness has also increased in recent years, with
emphasis shifting to health care and health consultation. As many
as 923,713 households have established files on health care.
</P>
<P>
The city has set up 1,185 healthcare service sites since 1993,
offering services to 2.6 million residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
