<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eugenic Measures Help Panda Cubs Grow Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Giant panda cub Jiujiu spent
his first birthday in his mother's arms recently at the Chengdu
Giant Panda Breeding Center in Southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Breast-fed since birth, Jiujiu weighs 49 kilograms, much
heavier than other weanlings.
</P>
<P>
Prolonging the breast-feeding period is one of the new eugenic
measures for raising pandas.
</P>
<P>
Panda cubs used to be weaned after three months so their
mothers could continue to mate and breed in the next year. But
research shows that many weanlings stop growing at two or three
years old. Experts now believe that early weaning is one of the
major factors for the poor health of the cubs.
</P>
<P>
To solve this problem, the center cooperated with the Atlanta
Zoo in the U.S. to begin the eugenic project for giant pandas last
year.
</P>
<P>
Scientists established the family trees of giant pandas by
means of DNA tests. This effort helped avoid inbreeding in a group
of pandas and resulted in healthier cubs.
</P>
<P>
Mother pandas are now kept with their cubs for more than one
year so the little pandas can get better care.
</P>
<P>
Senior zoologist Yu Jianqiu said these eugenic measures will
reduce the breeding of pandas, but breast-feeding can provide
better nutrition and immunity for the cubs. And cubs will learn
more living skills from their mothers.
</P>
<P>
The Chengdu Giant Panda Breeding Center is the only
professional panda research center in China. Covering more than 30
hectares, it simulates the panda's natural environment.
</P>
<P>
A female giant panda gives birth to one or two cubs annually,
but experts believe it is difficult for pandas to mate naturally
in the breeding center. Only 24 percent of the females will breed,
so the birth rate is very low.
</P>
<P>
There are about 1,000 giant pandas in the world, mainly
in China's Sichuan, Gansu and Shaanxi provinces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0192 </DOCNO>
