<P>
On Monday, the two countries signed six documents, including an
agreement on 1998-1999 financial cooperation under which Germany
will provide 25 million marks in aid.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade has developed rapidly in recent years, reaching
120 million marks (about 70 million U.S. dollars) in 1997 or 6.2
times more than in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
