<HEADLINE> China Pledges Support for Tumen River Valley Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUNCHUN (Jilin Province), September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese
Government will, as always, support international cooperation in
the Tumen River Valley, said a Chinese foreign trade official.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guangxiang, vice-minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, made this pledge while attending the ongoing
second international investment and trade fair of the Tumen River
Valley which opened Monday in Hunchun in northeast China's Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
The vice-minister also said that China will cooperate with
Russia and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), as
well as international organizations, in advancing development of
the region under the principles of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The three-day fair is sponsored jointly by the United Nations
Industrial Development Organizations (UNIDO), the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and the Jilin Provincial Government,
with approval from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Businesses from 11 countries and regions including China, the
United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea, Russia and the DPRK
are attending the fair.
</P>
<P>
The Tumen River flows along the Sino-DPRK border and empties
into the Sea of Japan in Chinese territory bordering Russia.
</P>
<P>
According to a plan mapped out by the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), an investment of 30 billion
U.S. dollars will be required to build the Tumen River Delta into
a global transportation and communications, trade and finance
center over the next two decades.
</P>
<P>
The first Tumen River Valley international investment and trade
fair was held in the Korean Autonomous Prefecture of Yanbian in
northeast China's Jilin Province two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
