<HEADLINE> New Zealand Sees Fewer Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 22 (Xinhua) -- There were 93,640 visitor
arrivals in New Zealand in August, 5,580 or 6 percent fewer than a
year
ago, according to Tuesday's media release from Statistics New
Zealand.
</P>
<P>
For the whole year to August 1998, New Zealand saw 1.453
million
visitors, also 6 percent fewer than the previous year's total of
1.54
million.
</P>
<P>
Last month, visitor arrivals from Asia totaled 24,280, a drop
of
9,610 or 28 percent compared with August 1997. This was mostly due
to a
fall of 7,420 in the number of visitors from the Republic of
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the number of visitors to New Zealand has

generally been decreasing since the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In August, the country suffered a net loss of 1,260 permanent
and
long-term migrants, compared with a gain of 590 a year ago.
</P>
<P>
For the year to August, there was a net migration loss of
2,840,
compared with net gains of 14,490 and 28,390 for the two previous
years
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
