<HEADLINE> South China Cracking Down On Foreign Exchange Infractions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Zengcheng Branch of the
Guangdong Development Bank recently had its right to deal in
foreign exchange revoked because of involvement in illegal foreign
exchange dealings.
</P>
<P>
The branch was one of 5 local banks that were penalized by
Guangdong Province foreign exchange authorities for foreign
exchange violations in a recent crack-down that came in response
to a resurgence of illegal practices in foreign exchange
transactions in the coastal province, adjacent to Hong Kong and
Macao.
</P>
<P>
New measures worked out by the Guangdong Branch of the State
Foreign Exchange Administration recently demand better management
on foreign exchange payments for exports, foreign exchange
settlements, and exchanges by individuals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
