<HEADLINE> Iranians, Afghan Refugees Clash in Central Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Clashes have taken place
between scores of Iranians and Afghan refugees in an Iranian
central province, the Iran Daily newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Morteza Lotfullah Khajouei, head of Aliens and
Foreign Immigration Affairs Bureau of Isfahan Province, as saying
that the clashes occurred on September 11 in the northern part of
the province.
</P>
<P>
Forty Iranians, "who apparently took advantage of the present
circumstances," provoked the conflicts, Khajouei said, adding that
a number of Afghan refugees were injured in the skirmishes.
</P>
<P>
He said 39 Iranians were detained and 30 of them were then
released on bail.
</P>
<P>
The official was referring to the growing tensions between Iran
and the Afghan Taliban group, whose militia killed eight Iranian
diplomats and a reporter last month in northern Afghanistan.
Angered Iranians have vowed to take revenge.
</P>
<P>
Khajouei said the Iranians instigating the turmoil considered
that the Afghan refugees have squeezed their employment
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
They opposed the residence and employment of the refugees in
the province and clashed with the Afghans before, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
