<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- About 800 soldiers from
South Africa and Botswana entered Lesotho Tuesday morning to help
the embattled government of Prime Minister Pakalitha Mosisili,
said sources reaching here from Maseru.
</P>
<P>
The peace-keeping forces exchanged gunfire with opposition
supporters at the Royal Palace of king Letsie III soon after
their arrival in Maseru, capital of the mountain kingdom, which
is bordering with South Africa, witnesses said.
