source said.
</P>
<P>
The military intervention follows unsuccessful attempts by a
Southern African Development Community (SADC) team headed by
Safety and Security Minister Sydney Mufamadi to mediate a
negotiated settlement to the crisis triggered by opposition
claims that the May 23 election in the country was rigged.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho has been wrecked by instability since early August,
with the capital Maseru paralyzed by unrest and the government
unable to rely on the support of its security forces after an
insurrection in the Lesotho Defense Force.
</P>
<P>
The South African National Defense Force said in a statement
that the Lesotho government requested military intervention from
the heads of state of Botswana, Mozambique, South Africa and
Zimbabwe to restore normality to his country. 
