<HEADLINE> Tanasugarn, Li Advance to Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Thai Tamarine Tanasugarn and
Chinese Li Fang routed their respective opponents to advance to
the second round of the Princess Cup tennis tournament here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai woman rallied from 0-3 in the second set to eliminate
Japanese wild card Yuka Yoshida 6-4, 6-3 by winning six games in
a row.
</P>
<P>
Chinese top player Li Fang defeated South Korean qualifier
Jeon Mi-Ra 6-2, 6-0 with ease.
</P>
<P>
Tanasugarn, who ranked 47th, said "I expected it to be a tough
match, because Yuka is a tough girl, she always fights back.
Today, she played very well, too, trying to keep every ball back.
I just played my best." said Tanasugarn.
</P>
<P>
For her victory, Li said "it was a little difficult in this
wind, but not too bad. The score looks easy, but every game was
tough. I just hit a couple of forehands here and there and she
made a lot of mistakes."
</P>
<P>
Japan's top player Ai Sugiyama pulled out with a foot injury
that forced her to abandon a US Open second round match, but
number two Naoko Sawamatsu survived the first hurdle of her final
WTA tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sawamatsu breezed past Anna Smashnova of Israel 6-1, 6-2 and
set up a second-round meeting against former world number one
Monica Seles.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Seles, seeded second, and other top three
seeds received first-round byes. 
</P>
