<HEADLINE> Three Die in U.S. Southwest Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Three illegal immigrants
died after their van plunged into a canal in New Mexico in
southwestern United States, police said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Local police Sergeant Ed Miranda said eight people were riding
in the van, but the other five were rescued by policemen and
civilians.
</P>
<P>
Miranda identified the three killed as Facunco P. Samaniego,
Julio Nino and Gilberto Chariez, all illegal immigrants from
neighboring Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the van, Maria C. Flores, a 40-year-old woman,
was arrested immediately and charged with three counts of vehicle
homicide.
</P>
<P>
Miranda said alcohol and excessive speed might have caused the
accident, which occurred about five miles south of Las Cruces, a
city just north of the U.S.-Mexican border. 
</P>
