<HEADLINE> Three Die in U.S. Southwest Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Three people died after
their van plunged into a canal in New Mexico, according to reports
reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Local police officer Ed Miranda said eight people was riding in
the ill-fated van when the accident took place.
</P>
<P>
The other five people were rescued by policemen and civilians
who were in the area.
</P>
<P>
Miranda said the three killed were Facunco P. Samaniego, Julio
Nino and Gilberto Chariez, all illegal immigrants from the
neighboring Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the van, Maria C. Flores, is a 40-year-old woman
who was arrested immediately and charged with three counts of
vehicle homicide.
</P>
<P>
Miranda said alcohol and excessive speeding may have caused the
accident, which occurred about eight kilometers south of Las
Cruces, a city inside New Mexico just north of the U.S.-Mexican
border. 
