<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Launches Campaign to Rebuild Homeland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo Monday called for a concerted national effort to rebuild
and restore parts of the country devastated by a series of natural
disasters these past few months.
</P>
<P>
In a speech launching the "national ecological restoration
campaign," Zedillo urged the participation of all citizens
regardless of their religious or ideological differences.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has a long-term strategy that seeks to
reverse the chronic and complex process of environmental
deterioration, which is posing a grave threat to the interests and
welfare of the nation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to protect forest areas in Mexico and not
to turn them into farm land.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo recalled recent natural disasters in the country,
including hurricane "Paulina," forest fires, freezing weather, and
droughts caused by the "El Nino" phenomenon, as well as heavy rain
and floods in Chiapas state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
