<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Banks Extend Credit to Tea Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's commercial banks
will continue to extend credit to firms exporting tea to
crisis-hit Russia in a bid to protect the tea industry in the
country.
</P>
<P>
This decision followed a high-powered conference between
government officials and representatives of commercial banks last
weekend, according to Finance Ministry sources Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The government at the meeting urged the bankers to continue
with the credit facilities to exporters as the Russian currency
crisis is expected to blow over soon, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Russia is Sri Lanka's biggest tea market and the Russian
currency crisis had affected tea prices at most tea auction
centers recently.
</P>
<P>
Price at the Colombo auction at present continues to fall and
Sri Lanka's tea small-holders are the most affected. 
</P>
