<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Millions Alerted to Hurricane "George" in Caribbean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Millions of people have been
alerted to the coming hurricane "George" through the Caribbean
region as it closed in dangerously to Puerto Rico on Monday.
</P>
<P>
After strong tides and heavy raining hit the northern part of
Lesser Antilles, the hurricane, now a little weakened, closed on
Monday afternoon to Puerto Rico, where authorities and population
had reportedly made necessary preparations.
</P>
<P>
Classified as number three on the Saffir-Simpson scale of five,
"George" has sustained winds at 175 kilometers per hour, with
threats directed also at the Dominican Republic, where a state of
alert was declared.
</P>
<P>
In Santo Domingo, the Civilian Defense installed a Center of
Operations and started to put up shelters for possible victims of
the disaster.
</P>
<P>
In Cuba, the Civilian Defense raised alert in five eastern
provinces, which were the hardest-hit by a long drought earlier
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
