<HEADLINE> Flood Victims in Inner Mongolia Settled for Winter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Residents in the
flood-stricken areas of northern China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region have all been provided with proper housing and sufficient
food and clothing in preparation for the coming winter, according
to local government officials.
</P>
<P>
Beginning in August, the local government began to make
arrangements for the settlement of these families so they could be
settled before the freezing winter comes. Temporary, public, and
vacant houses are being used to accommodate those who lost their
homes in the floods.
</P>
<P>
The local government also adopted measures such as grain loans
from the government, donations from neighboring cities, and other
effective means to ensure sufficient food and clothing for the
flood victims.
</P>
<P>
The Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region suffered seven
devastating floods this summer which destroyed 178,600 houses and
left some 300,000 people homeless. More than one-million people
were left in desperate need of food and clothing.
</P>
<P>
At present, the local government plans to allocate one thousand
yuan to each flood-affected family, along with subsidies for
rebuilding houses and a two-month grain supply. Some 13,500 tons
of donated grain and 1.8 million pieces of donated clothes have
already been distributed to the flood victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
