<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Step Up Levies Control (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Levies that by their nature represent government functions will
be replaced by taxes and included in the government budget, while
a limited number of levies that are compatible with international
practices will be allowed to remain, he said.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, China's related departments have cancelled 29
items of administrative operating charges and 147 unreasonable
fund items, which together will reduce the burden on enterprises
by some 13 billion yuan a year.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that over the past year local authorities
throughout the country have revoked a total of 20,700 items of
irrational charges on firms, involving a total value of 49.3
billion yuan, and handled more than 12,000 cases of illegal
levies.
</P>
<P>
The State Council issued a circular recently demanding various
localities to clear up all administrative operating charges, fines
and fund-raising items before this October, with major attention
given to such industries and departments as electricity, railways
and public security.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance revealed that pilot projects will be
launched to turn charges into taxes in rural areas, with the aim
of lowering total levies on farmers to under five percent of their
average annual per capita income.
</P>
<P>
In order to create effective levies management procedures and
establish a sound taxation system, the State Council and related
departments have published a series of policies and regulations
involving the management of extra-budgetary funds, the
rectification of unreasonable levies on firms and stricter control
on receipts.
</P>
<P>
At the same time. the State Council is also making efforts to
bring the government's fiscal revenue and expenditure mechanisms
into accord with market practices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
