<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Vocational Education for Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Union University has
begun making advanced vocational courses available to the
disabled, and the first group of 27 students have already started
their studies.
</P>
<P>
These advanced courses for the handicapped include learning
massage for blind people, and the deaf becoming skilled at
decorative advertisements. Students will spend three years
learning these specialties.
</P>
<P>
At present, Beijing has 24 schools for the disabled, including
one for blind people, six for the deaf, and 17 for the mentally
retarted. There are also 74 special courses attached to primary
and secondary mainstream schools. 
</P>
