<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Deforestation Causes Economic Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka suffers an annual
loss of around 6,000 million rupees (91 million U.S. dollars) as a
result of direct and indirect deforestation, according to the
Environment Ministry Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey on economic costs of environmental degradation
from the ministry confirmed that Sri Lanka's deforestation rate is
one of the highest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The survey has revealed a great need to address environmental
problems and new issues emerging daily in a more effective manner.
</P>
<P>
The existing legislation pertaining to environmental protection
is not adequate to address the fast-changing environmental
scenario.
</P>
<P>
In addition to deforestation, acute coastal degradation also
results in a loss of around 55 million dollars annually, the
survey said.
</P>
<P>
Because of administrative lapses and loopholes in the
environmental laws, effective action could not be taken to arrest
the situation, a senior official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
