<HEADLINE> Panama's Revenue Rises in First Eight Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Panama's revenue in the
first eight months of this year amounted to more than 1.06 billion
U.S. dollars, 66.4 million dollars more than that in the same
period last year, an official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo Mirones, vice minister of the Treasure and Public
Finance, said that in the January-August period, taxes totaled
713.8 million dollars, 15.7 million dollars more than the
corresponding period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said the taxes from real estate were 123.7 million dollars
and the import duties stood at 153.6 million dollars, 16 percent
and 17 percent higher than the last January-August period
respectively.
</P>
<P>
State-owned companies earned 142.7 million dollars in the
period, 27.7 million dollars more than last year, the vice
minister said. 
</P>
