<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Step Up Levies Control (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 22 (Xinhua) -- For China's fiscal and
taxation departments, clearing up levies has become the
core of their work.
</P>
<P>
Sources from related departments said that effective measures
are being introduced to rectify various levies in order to create
an ideal environment for state fiscal and tax management.
</P>
<P>
The fiscal levy system reform carried out in 1994 has been
successful, with industrial and commercial tax revenues increasing
some 100 billion yuan, or 16 percent, annually.
</P>
<P>
However, exorbitant levies by local governments at various
levels have seriously hurt state revenues and resulted in heavy
burdens on businesses and individuals.
</P>
<P>
Incomplete statistics show that various levies and funds
approved by the State Council and the ministries, combined with
those approved by local governments, have exceeded 2,000 items,
with a total value of more than 40 percent of all fiscal revenues.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, China's fiscal revenues accounted for
some 10 percent of its gross domestic product (GDP), and compared
with other developing countries, Chinese businesses pay
comparatively less in taxes.
</P>
<P>
However, many firms are subject to more types of levies, other
than taxes, and the total amount of these levies often equals that
of the taxes they pay.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that at present the combined value of taxes and
levies on Chinese firms accounts for 25 to 30 percent of the the
GDP, surpassing the average level of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Finance Xiang Huaicheng said that rampant levies
introduced not only disturb orderly distribution and hurt fiscal
revenues, but also do harm to the image of the government and, to
some extent, make it easier for corruption.
</P>
<P>
He said that measures will be taken to deal with various levies
in terms of their nature, category and circumstances. "Illegal and
irrational levies will be definitely revoked," he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980922.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
