<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The remains of former President Yang Shangkun, a veteran
Chinese revolutionary, who died on September 14 at the age of 92,
were cremated in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Party and government officials, including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng,
Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing, paid their final
respects yesterday morning at the No. 301 Hospital of the People's
Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
-- Residents in east China's Jiangsu Province have conquered
rampant summer flooding and are working diligently to achieve this
year's annual growth target of 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Scholars, lawyers and trade and insurance representatives
from nearly 20 countries and regions met yesterday at the Third
International Conference on Maritime Law in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The four-day conference, sponsored by the China Maritime Law
Association (CMLA) and the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade, will cover marine insurance, maritime
shipping laws, charters, detaining ships, liability, ship
financing, salvage, arbitration and litigation, regional
conflicts, and international marine safety.
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Chunyun, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of
the Chinese National People's Congress, met yesterday with a
delegation from the Korean Foundation, headed by foundation
president Lee Joung-Binn.
</P>
<P>
