"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A national publicity campaign on voluntary blood donation
will take place in the run-up to the launch of the Blood Donation
Law on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The law, the first of its kind in China, was approved by the
National People's Congress Standing Committee at the end of last
year. It lays down the rights and duties of Chinese citizens
relating to the donation and use of blood as well as standardizing
the practices of blood collection and supply institutes.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Oceanographic Administration (SOA) is drafting an
updated and authoritative report on China's marine
environment. Analysis showed a constant deterioration in the
quality of the coastal sea area environment and an expansion in
the polluted area. Pollution accidents were more common and
environmental problems more complicated.
</P>
<P>
-- China confiscated 5.42 billion yuan (653 million US dollars)
worth of smuggled goods during the first eight months of the year,
the General Administration of Customs announced.  
