<HEADLINE> Patent Approved For New Chinese Watch Design </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Patent Bureau
recently approved a patent for an invention of Kiu Tai Yu, a watch
designer in Hong Kong, for the Kiu Mystery Tourbillon, which he
calls "the King of watches".
</P>
<P>
It is the first patent accorded a Chinese for sophisticated
mechanical watch works. Kiu blends the traditional Chinese art of
seal cutting and calligraphy in watchmaking.
</P>
<P>
Kiu, who is a native of Jiangsu Province, began his love affair
with antiques and watchmaking when he was just 12 years old. He
moved to Hong Kong in 1980.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, Kiu made his first invention, called the 'tourbillon',
which won him the title of great master of watch design in Asia,
and in the past 7 years he has completed 14 different models.
</P>
