<HEADLINE> Milutinovic to Coach MetroStars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Bora Milutinovic, the
only man to guide four different teams into the second round of
the World Cup, was hired on Monday to coach the New York-New
Jersey MetroStars.
</P>
<P>
Thus, the Serbian-born Milutinovic became the club's fifth
coach in three years with a contract running to the end of the
season.
</P>
<P>
The club saw the departure of Brazilian Carlos Alberto
Parreira who left in December to coach Saudi Arabia in the World
Cup.
</P>
<P>
The MetroStars clinched a playoff berth last month, but lost
their last six matches, fallen from second to third in the
Eastern Conference and dropped to 14-17 with one game remaining
before the post-season.
</P>
<P>
To his credit, Milutinovic led Mexico to the quarterfinals at
the 1986 World Cup, its highest finish.
</P>
<P>
He took over Costa Rica just before the 1990 World Cup and
stunned many by getting it into the second round and guided the
United States for the second round in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic appeared again on the world scene in France this
summer, guiding Nigeria into the second round before it was
eliminated by Denmark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
