<HEADLINE> Bosnich in Hot Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The English Football
Association charged Monday goalkeeper Mark Bosnich with
misconduct following allegations that he swore at fans during
Aston Villa's goalless draw against Everton.
</P>
<P>
A police report was filed following the incident that
supposedly took place on August 15.
</P>
<P>
One of the complaints that lead to the report came from a
member of the Mersey tunnel Authority's private police force, the
other from a member of the public.
</P>
<P>
Bosnich refutes the claims, saying, "This is all ridiculous.
It never happened.
</P>
<P>
"When the final whistle went I just turned round and made a
gesture of triumph to the crowd because we had won a hard-earned
point."
</P>
<P>
In October 1996, Bosnich landed himself in trouble after
delivering a Nazi-style salute to Tottenham fans.
</P>
<P>
He subsequently received a formal warning from the FA
regarding his future conduct.
</P>
<P>
Bosnich has 14 days to reply to the fresh claims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
