<HEADLINE> Eight Countries Meet on Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from
eight countries met on Monday at the U.N. headquarters here to
defuse tension between Iran and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and his counterparts from
Pakistan, Russia, Tajikistan, the United States and Uzbekistan
attended the U.N.-sponsored meeting.
</P>
<P>
What is impressive at the meeting is that foreign minister of
Iran, one of parties in the escalating tension, was not present
at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Asked why the Iranian foreign minister failed to attend the
meeting, Fred Eckhard, spokesman for U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan, said, "I don't know why it is, you have to ask him."
</P>
<P>
However, Iranian sources simply said that Kamal Kharrazi,
Iranian foreign minister, had to accompany Iranian President
Mohammad Khatami, who took the floor on Monday afternoon at the
general debate of the 53rd General Assembly session.
</P>
<P>
Javad Zarif, deputy foreign minister of Iran and permanent
representatives to the United Nations from Tajikistan and
Turkmenistan were present at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
