<HEADLINE> Bowling Roof Collapse Injures 25 in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- About 25 people were injured
on Monday when the roof of a bowling alley collapsed near the
Canadian city of Montreal, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Eleven of the injured were taken to hospital, while the rest
were examined at the scene for less serious injuries.
</P>
<P>
"The people taken to hospital mostly had head, neck and back
injuries," police was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
There were some 175 people in the building playing when its
roof cave in.  
</P>
</TEXT>
